      What is AbortSignal any () API?
      AbortSignal: any() static method

      Note: This feature is available in Web Workers. The AbortSignal. any() static method takes an iterable of abort signals and returns an AbortSignal . The returned abort signal is aborted when any of the input iterable abort signals are aborted.      2024. 5. 7.

      How to cancel a fetch request in JS?
      AbortController: abort() method

      The abort() method of the AbortController interface aborts an asynchronous operation before it has completed. This is able to abort fetch requests, the consumption of any response bodies, or streams.      2024. 5. 7.
